## 5. Risks and Assumptions

### 5.1 Risks

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |
| SM prompt out of sync across 4 locations | High | Medium | Sync script (sync-from-source.ps1) ensures consistency |
| jira.conf accidentally committed with wrong project key | Low | Low | File is simple text, easy to fix manually |
| Jira MCP server unavailable during project query | Medium | Low | SM falls back to file-based status only |

### 5.2 Assumptions

* Jira MCP server is properly configured in user’s environment
* User has access to query tickets in the target project
* Workspace root is the correct location for jira.conf
* All 4 SM prompt locations are accessible for update

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Category | Requirement | Details |
| Performance | Project query response | Should return within 5 seconds for projects with ≤50 tickets |
| Security | No sensitive data in jira.conf | Only project prefix stored, no URLs or tokens |
| Compatibility | Backward compatible | Existing ticket-level commands (KSA-13 tạo BRD) continue to work unchanged |
| Maintainability | Single source of truth | SM prompt maintained in source, synced to other locations via script |

